clock in the morning we were made to rise for Appell and in ten minutes everybody had to stand in formation ready to march to work again. And so it lasted for quite a time. In our lager . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2231.045","u": "This concludes Spool 122, by Udel Stopnitsky from Bedzin. We are going over to Spool 123. The record is taken at H&#195;nonville near Paris in a Kibbutz which is managed by the Agudah, and the educational part is run by the ORT. Paris, September the 12th, 1946. Illinois Institute of Technology Wire Recording."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2270.479","u": "France, September the 12th, 1943. France, September the 12th, 1943. [The interviewer gave obviously the wrong year because Stopnitsky was talking of events which occurred in 1943; the year of course was 1946. &#226;D.P.B.] H&#195;nonville, fifty kilometers from Paris at the Kibbutz of the Agudah. Udel Stopnitsky, thirty-one years old, continues from Spool 122nd. This is spool 123."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2292.962","u": "[In Yiddish] Now, then, you were somewhere near Breslau?"},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "2295.971","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2296.268","u": "And you worked there . . ."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "2297.394","u": "We worked in Krupp&#39;s factory. We manufactured cannons whether we wanted to or not . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2303.217","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "2303.548","u": "We had to work. And that is how it was there. But in time Russia started a counter-offensive."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2313.083","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "2313.632","u": "And it was said at the times around January to March, 1945[?] [he speaks not very clearly and the year is not distinguishable] . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2317.714","u": "Yes . . ."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "2318.650","u": "And P