 the schools?"},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4185.654","u": "Yes, the ORT has given us the means to open the schools."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4188.343","u": "Now, for instance, those who are learning carpentry, do they work all day in the carpentry shop . . ."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4194.458","u": "They work from nine to one and from three to six."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4200.000","u": "So that&#39;s how they work in the carpentry shop."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4201.382","u": "In the carpentry shop."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4201.847","u": "Then they are not working in the orchard?"},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4203.440","u": "No, they must learn carpentry. And those who work in the garden work nowhere else but in the garden because they have to learn gardening. In the evening, at six in the evening, they wash themselves, and everybody goes to study the chapter which is being taught by the Rabbi. That is being done every day."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4218.644","u": "What do they learn?"},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4219.430","u": "A chapter from the Talmud, they study the Talmud all together."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4222.313","u": "And tell me, what is there the Yeshiva doing."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4224.468","u": "The Yeshiva studies all day."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4226.721","u": "This Yeshiva does not belong to the Kibbutz?"},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4229.265","u": "No."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4229.948","u": "But they eat with you?"},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4231.186","u": "That takes place in form of hospitality since they are on their way to America and they have no place where they could eat Kosher and they eat only Kosher . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4237.863","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4238.202","u": "So they were assigned a wing of our building and we eat together and they all sleep there."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4243.320","u": "Tell me, where do you get Kosher meat?"},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4246.323","u": "In Paris there is a Kosher meat market."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4249.092","u": "There is a Kosher meat market . . ."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4250.211","u": "Yes, one can get Kosher sausage . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4252.751","u": "And that is being brought over here . . ."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4253.801","u": "Yes, and . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4256.914","u": "You have no shohet here?"},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4258.434","u": "We have here two shohets, but one does not slaughter here because there is no slaughter house."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4261.959","u": "Can&#39;t you get chickens?"},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4263.380","u": "We have no chickens here, we don&#39;t have here in general such things. We have to buy everything. The whole week we do not eat meat."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4270.595","u": "You don&#39;t eat it the whole week?"},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4271.828","u": "No, only on the Sabbath, Friday at night, and Saturday in the daytime."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4275.640","u": "Oh, then the whole week you eat vegetarian food."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4278.626","u": "We eat potatoes with something else, with turnips, or we eat noodles with peas, but meat is not being eaten the whole week. Not only because&#226;we could get meat&#226;but we have no money."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4289.118","u": "H-um."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4289.679","u": "The 100 francs a day are not enough, could not be stretched that we could buy meat every day."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4295.644","u": "And the UNRRA does not supply you with products?"},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4298.711","u": "We get nothing. Even when they gave us [foodstuffs] not every product could be eaten, but the things we could eat . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4303.348","u": "What do you mean, you couldn&#39;t eat it?"},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4304.146","u": "Not every product is Kosher."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4305.700","u": "Oh, that is the reason."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4306.624","u": "But even the products that one could eat, we also do not get. We get no products whatsoever, only that what we buy for our money."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4316.440","u": "[In English] This concludes . . . this concludes Spool 123 at thirty-one minutes of the indicator. The person reporting was Udel Stopnitsky who is now the teacher . . . eh, the head of the organization. He arrived here only about two weeks ago and has been suggested or imposed by the central Jewish organization, or by the central Agudah organization. H&#195;nonville, near Paris, September the 12th, 1946. An Illinois Institute of Technology wire recording."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4363.422","u": "[In Yiddish] Well, I thank you very much, Mr. Stopnitsky. It was a very good report. I have hard a lot of stories and, nevertheless, you have told me some things new. One constantly hears new things. It is never enough."},    {"who": "Udel Stopnitsky", "start": "4378.339","u": "If you should listen for months, for months at a stretch you will not hear everything that the Polish Jews went through. It is very much but let it be enough because all the Polish Jews have contributed to the tradgedy."}        ]
    }
